-- Del Potro Beats Benneteau in Rotterdam; Azarenka Downs Williams
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2013-02-17T18:39:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-17/del-potro-defeats-benneteau-to-win-rotterdam-world-tennis-title.html
Juan Martin del Potro  of Argentina
beat  Julien Benneteau  of France in straight sets to win the
Rotterdam World Tennis title today.  World No. 7 Del Potro won 7-6 (7-2), 6-3, having lost in
last year’s final to  Roger Federer . Benneteau beat world No. 2
Federer in this year’s quarterfinals.  Victoria Azarenka  of Belarus beat  Serena Williams  of the
U.S. 7-6 (8-6), 2-6, 6-3 to defend her Qatar Open title.
Williams will replace Azarenka tomorrow at the top of the WTA
rankings.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
